<p>For example requireJS uses following syntax:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;script data-main="scripts/main" src="scripts/require.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and in its documentation you can read:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>data-main attribute tells require.js to load scripts/main.js after   require.js loads</p> </blockquote>  <ol> <li>How is that (script load-order) possible?</li> <li>If the name of the js-file was nomain.js, would the data-attribute be "data-nomain" ?</li> <li>I see no information about that in the html5 specification or am I looking at wrong place?</li> </ol>  <p>thank you</p>